### Role of Activation Functions
Activation functions introduce non-linearity, enabling neural networks to learn complex patterns. Without them, stacked linear layers would collapse to a single linear transformation (no matter how many layers). ReLU (Rectified Linear Unit: f(x)=max(0,x)) is popular because it's computationally efficient, mitigates vanishing gradients, and creates sparse activations. For multi-class classification, softmax converts outputs to probabilities: P(class_i)=e^{z_i}/Î£e^{z_j}, ensuring outputs sum to 1.

